\f1\b \cf4 \cb3 \strokec4 ## Appendix A: Evaluation Framework \'97 Metric Definitions
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Confusion-matrix components are computed per element per annotator:\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ```\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 TP = ((data[source_col] == 1) & (data[annotator_col] == 1)).sum()\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 FN = ((data[source_col] == 1) & (data[annotator_col] == 2)).sum()\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 FP = ((data[source_col] == 0) & (data[annotator_col] == 3)).sum()\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 TN = ((data[source_col] == 0) & (data[annotator_col] == "N/A")).sum()\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ```\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 | Symbol | Interpretation |\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 |--------|----------------|\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 | TP | Correctly extracted feature present in source |\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 | FN | Omission \'97 source present, not extracted |\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 | FP | Fabrication \'97 source absent, extracted anyway |\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 | TN | Correctly not extracted |\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\

\f1\b \cf8 \cb3 \strokec8 **Primary safety outcome:**
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ```\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Fabrication rate = FP / (FP + TN)\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ```\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 Statistical tests: One-sided exact McNemar (binomial on discordant pairs, \cf4 \strokec4 `alternative="greater"`\cf2 \strokec2 ) testing H1: AI metric > Human metric for diagnostic metrics, and H1: AI fabrication rate > Human fabrication rate for fabrication.\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\

\f1\b \cf4 \cb3 \strokec4 ## Appendix B: Source Document Feature Analysis
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 For each case, the following document-level features should be computed from OCR-extracted text:\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 -\cf2 \strokec2  Number of reports per case\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 -\cf2 \strokec2  Total token count / average tokens per report\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 -\cf2 \strokec2  Unique token ratio\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 -\cf2 \strokec2  Lexical diversity (type-token ratio)\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 -\cf2 \strokec2  Embedding variance (sentence-transformer or BERT)\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 -\cf2 \strokec2  Negation frequency\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 -\cf2 \strokec2  Uncertainty language frequency (e.g., "possible", "cannot exclude")\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 -\cf2 \strokec2  Table density (structured vs free-text ratio)\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 -\cf2 \strokec2  Cross-document semantic similarity (cosine similarity of document embeddings)\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 These features serve as predictors in downstream modeling of AI fabrication and omission.\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\

\f1\b \cf4 \cb3 \strokec4 ## Appendix C: Deidentification Pipeline for Scanned PDFs
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\

\f1\b \cf8 \cb3 \strokec8 **Purpose:**
\f0\b0 \cf2 \strokec2  OCR-based bounding-box redaction with black rectangles, applied to both source PDFs and the validation Excel spreadsheet.\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\

\f1\b \cf8 \cb3 \strokec8 **Dependencies:**
\f0\b0 \cf2 \strokec2  \cf4 \strokec4 `pymupdf`\cf2 \strokec2 , \cf4 \strokec4 `pytesseract`\cf2 \strokec2 , \cf4 \strokec4 `opencv-python`\cf2 \strokec2 , \cf4 \strokec4 `pillow`\cf2 \strokec2 , \cf4 \strokec4 `pandas`\cf2 \strokec2 , \cf4 \strokec4 `tqdm`\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\

\f1\b \cf8 \cb3 \strokec8 **Redaction rules (HIPAA-aligned):**
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 -\cf2 \strokec2  Email, phone, SSN, dates, ZIP codes, URLs, address patterns\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 -\cf2 \strokec2  MRN (context-based, with label lookahead)\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf7 \cb3 \strokec7 -\cf2 \strokec2  Contextual: if token matches a PHI label (Name, Patient, DOB, MRN), redact next N tokens on same line\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\

\f1\b \cf8 \cb3 \strokec8 **Key configuration:**
\f0\b0 \cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ```python\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec5 CONTEXT_LABELS = \{\cf6 \cb3 \strokec6 "name"\cf2 \cb3 \strokec5 , \cf6 \cb3 \strokec6 "patient"\cf2 \cb3 \strokec5 , \cf6 \cb3 \strokec6 "dob"\cf2 \cb3 \strokec5 , \cf6 \cb3 \strokec6 "dateofbirth"\cf2 \cb3 \strokec5 , \cf6 \cb3 \strokec6 "birth"\cf2 \cb3 \strokec5 , \cf6 \cb3 \strokec6 "mrn"\cf2 \cb3 \strokec5 , \cf6 \cb3 \strokec6 "acct"\cf2 \cb3 \strokec5 , \cf6 \cb3 \strokec6 "account"\cf2 \cb3 \strokec5 \}\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec5 redact_after_label_tokens = \cf9 \strokec9 6\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\cf2 \cb3 \strokec2 ```\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\

\f1\b \cf8 \cb3 \strokec8 **Patient mapping requirement:**
\f0\b0 \cf2 \strokec2  Deidentified outputs must retain a \cf4 \strokec4 `case_id \uc0\u8596  original_filename`\cf2 \strokec2  mapping table (stored separately in a secure location) to enable downstream observation-level linkage.\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\

\f1\b \cf8 \cb3 \strokec8 **Outputs:**
\f0\b0 \cf2 \strokec2  Redacted PDFs + CSV redaction log (file, page, status, redaction count, rules applied).\cf2 \cb1 \strokec2 \
\

